text:
you could enter {{name}} (without module.) in a text-field or directly into your HTML+Hubl area.
But this will print you the automaticaly generated name such as module_74567875. Not the "nice label".
It won't change the name of the module.

This can be done only in the template like
```{% module "module_1765697" path="@HubSpot/button", label="button 1", no_wrapper=True %}

{% module "module_1765697" path="@HubSpot/button", label="button 2", no_wrapper=True %}```
